386→                        <div id="content">Let $\alpha,\beta\in (0,1)$ and let $P(n)$ denote the largest prime divisor of $n$. Does the density of integers $n$ such that $P(n)&#60;n^{\alpha}$ and $P(n+1)&#60;(n+1)^\beta$ exist?<br></div>
